    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-28T22:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-28T22:42:00-05:00" n="75"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/2021: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Military Governor of Santo Domingo</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fuller</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="22" xml:id="d75fn22">Copy received in the Department of
                        State Dec. 30, 1918.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-28T23:02:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1918, 11.02 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following message is for the Department of State. Prospective investors in
                    1918 Dominican Bonds raise point that if $20,000,000 Bond[s] of 1908 are
                    redeemed prior to January 1938, the custom Receivership terminates &amp; 1918
                    bonds will therefore not have Amortization and interest guaranteed by U.S.
                    Collector of customs. Military Government’s interpretation of United States
                    Government’s consent issue 1918 bonds is that it constitutes an extension of
                    provision of American Dominican convention of 1918 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >1907</hi>]<note n="23" xml:id="d75fn23">
                        <ref target="frus1907p1#pg_307">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1907, pt. 1, p.
                        307</ref>.</note> until both loans are fully redeemed. Investors’
                    contentions tend to greatly reduce value of 1918 bonds. Strongly recommends
                    immediate decision <pb facs="0231" n="146" xml:id="pg_146"/> being given
                    confirming military Governor’s interpretation, original publication of decision
                    in financial publication. 1918 bonds lately issued. Prestige of military
                    Government will be greatly diminished if its interpretation is not upheld. Cable
                    advices of action requested. 12028.</p>
                <closer>[No signature indicated]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
